    "abstractNote": "\"John of Apamea, is the most important spiritual father for the development of mysticism in Syrian Christianity. Although he belongs to the West-Syrian tradition his influence is not restricted to this region and transcends all ecclesiastical boundaries. The importance of the writings of this hermit for Syrian spirituality is demonstrated by some collections of manuscripts. Elements of his mystology were even acknowledged in Nestorian circles.\" (p. 111)",
